table_foot: Note: Patients' demographics. p‐Values are from Wilcoxon Rank Sum tests or Fisher's Exact tests where appropriate. The bold value represent a significant Wilcoxon Rank Sum tests p < .001. Data shown are median (IQR) or n (%).Abbreviations: AES, Articulatory Error Score; ASRS v3, Apraxia of Speech Rating Scale version 3; CPIB, communicative participation item bank; MDS‐UPDRS III, Movement Disorder Society‐Unified Parkinson's Disease Rating Scale‐motor subscale; MoCA, Montreal Cognitive Assessment; WAB praxis, Western Aphasia Battery‐praxis component; WAB‐AQ, Western Aphasia Battery‐Aphasia Quotient (AQ).
